title: Catalina Breeze - Single
body: Fred Armisen is amazing. I actually heard this song before I watched the episode of Documentary Now!

title: How Lucky Am I? - Single
body: Favorite of the 2-3 Toxhards songs I've listened to. Relatable

title: Don't Let It Get Ya Down - Single
body: Why do white rappers always sound "like that"? Not too bad just a thing I can't get over. Only bumping for the Wax feature

title: Insomniatic
body: What a lame album. All points go to Like Woah. Sounds of childhood though. Potential Breakup Song starting an entire album of breakup songs is interesting. Hillary Duff started playing after and I didn't even notice

title: Nothing to Say - Single
body: Pretty voice. Good instrument stacks. Cute stabs and adlibs. I think that landline vox effect adds instant points. Easy swing perc section. Feel that

title: City Slicker EP
body: I love this ep Loretta especially. Dreamy wobbly synths

title: Set do shonci
body: I don't speak portuguese. Not the point of this though. CHEGOU 3 carries and is in the daily rotation. That song alone gets 5#

title: Buck
body: Is this r&b/soul? I guess so. The first song reminds me of me trying to sing Prince in the shower. Cool enough guitar and keys. Pretty boring

title: Level Select
body: I think I used some of these songs in some blender renders? Good progressions and not too repetitive like other beep boop tunes can get. Neat samples. The ps2 menu had such a mysterious vibe. Now everything's netflix menus... Anyways, chill music with Polygon Dreamscape being my favorite
